faithcards.title: Evil Shall not Destroy me!
faithcards.scripture:
1 Samuel 4:1-11

4 So the people sent to Shiloh, that they might bring from thence the ark of the covenant of the LORD of hosts, which dwelleth between the cherubims: and the two sons of Eli, Hophni and Phinehas, were there with the ark of the covenant of God.

5 And when the ark of the covenant of the LORD came into the camp, all Israel shouted with a great shout, so that the earth rang again.

6 And when the Philistines heard the noise of the shout, they said, What meaneth the noise of this great shout in the camp of the Hebrews? And they understood that the ark of the LORD was come into the camp.

10 And the Philistines fought, and Israel was smitten, and they fled every man into his tent: and there was a very great slaughter; for there fell of Israel thirty thousand footmen.

11 And the ark of God was taken; and the two sons of Eli, Hophni and Phinehas, were slain.
faithcards.prayers:
LET US PRAYER

  1. Let God cleanse His church of evil and deceptive leadership.
  2. Let God santify the believers in the body of Christ by his Word and by the blood of our resurrected Lord, Jesus Christ.
  3. Let God give us godly political leaders in the society; such that have integrity, decency and true reverence for God.
  4. Let holiness and righteousness be entroned in our families and our lives
  5. Let no family lose their children to the diabolic attacks of evil like Eli did
  6. Let nothing kill or destroy that which belongs to us. We shall live blessed lives.
faithcards.study:
Who Carries the ark?

1 Samuel 4:1-11

Our nation and lives are likened to that of God’s people, Israel. The more they compromised and accommodated unrighteousness, the more God’s true power was lost among them. It was unfortunate that the corrupt sons of Eli, Hophni and Phinehas happened to become the bearers of God’s holy ark. It goes to show how and why the ark must have become ineffective in the face of filth that God allowed his ark to be captured by terrified Philistines.

Shouldn’t we re-examine today’s church and those that lead in it? Shouldn’t we take a second look at the kind of leaders we hand our nations to? Those who carried the ark of God unjustly died in the face of battle. Their self-confidence or pride could not save them. We pray that the life of evil will not ruin us, not ruin our businesses, not ruin our families and not ruin our nations, in the name of Jesus Christ. Amen.
faithcards.faith:
FAITH WORDS

  • I am created, saved and redeemed to live in the holiness and righteousness of God.
  • Evil, no matter the source or origin, shall not bring doom to me, it shall not destroy me or my family.
  • Satan and his unclean spirit have lost their battles against the church of Christ. They shall fail in any attempt to pollute the church of Christ on earth.
  • This is my week of victory, by the righteousness and holiness of God, I obtain victory over the forces that fight against me.
  • Holy, Holy, Holy is the Lord God Almighty. By the power of His Holiness, I take possession of my blessings. For upon Mount Zion there shall be Holiness and I possess my possessions.
faithcards.declarations:
DECLARATION OF FAITH

My Life is designed by the best, for the best, and with the best. I shall, therefore, experience and enjoy the best of life. In Jesus’ name. Amen

faithcards.title: I shall not be a Slave!
faithcards.scripture:
1 Samuel 4:6-11

6  And when the Philistines heard the noise of the shout, they said, What meaneth the noise of this great shout in the camp of the Hebrews? And they understood that the ark of the LORD was come into the camp.

7  And the Philistines were afraid, for they said, God is come into the camp. And they said, Woe unto us! for there hath not been such a thing heretofore.

8  Woe unto us! who shall deliver us out of the hand of these mighty Gods? these are the Gods that smote the Egyptians with all the plagues in the wilderness.

9  Be strong, and quit yourselves like men, O ye Philistines, that ye be not servants unto the Hebrews, as they have been to you: quit yourselves like men, and fight.

10  And the Philistines fought, and Israel was smitten, and they fled every man into his tent: and there was a very great slaughter; for there fell of Israel thirty thousand footmen.

11  And the ark of God was taken; and the two sons of Eli, Hophni and Phinehas, were slain.
faithcards.prayers:
Let Us Pray

Bind the operations of the Spirit of Fear in or around you. Refuse to be weakened by fear.

Pray for confidence and boldness to be restored in the church. A righteous church is a bold church.

Pray for righteousness within the local church.

Bind and Cast out any spirit intent on enslaving you. If you do not fight, you might become a slave to the ones that overpower you. Refuse the identity of a slave.

Pray for the grace to face the things that are difficult for you. All things are possible to them that believe.

Present all the projects that scare you before God and ask for strength. Take on the strength of Christ as he had when he faced the cross, let him activate your inner might.
faithcards.study:
Be Determined

We have lost count of the number of people that have failed in life because they gave up too quickly or became too afraid to stand and fight for what they believed. Life is going to through us challenges even from forces and factors greater than us. Until we grow the inner strength to face those things that scare us the most, we might never get to win our battles.

The Philistines knew that they were up against a God that defeated great nations. The shout in the camps of Israel terrified them. Someone got up among them and inspired them: “Fight or you become slaves”. It is that simple. If you are not ready to face life’s battle and win it, then you are likely to spend your time serving those who have.

Change your confessions; take up a stand. Refuse to become a slave to anyone or anything. If it seems unconquerable, get up and fight your way to victory.

If you must reach heights in life, know that your fight determines your flight.
faithcards.faith:
Confessions of Faith

  1. I shall not be intimidated by Satan or by failure
  2. I shall not give up faith or hope for I am a child of God
  3. I shall stand strong in the face of adversities till I win
  4. I shall overcome all challenges that come my way by the grace of Christ Jesus my Lord
  5. I shall not become Satan’s slave
  6. I shall not serve failure or defeat
  7. I shall win for I was created a winner.
faithcards.declarations:
DECLARATION OF FAITH

I am free, made free, born free, set free. I shall not be enslaved by fear, man or challenges. I choose to live free, reign free and stay free. In the name of Jesus. Amen.
faithcards.benedictions:
Faith Decree

I shall not be a slave to Sin; I shall not be a slave to Poverty; I shall not be a slave to bad habits; I shall not be a slave to Sicknesses; I shall not be a slave to curses; I shall not be a slave to Satan, I shall not be a slave to Failure; I shall not be a slave to Hell: IN JESUS NAME. Amen
